  "text": "Taken together, the nomogram proposed by Kattan et al was able to predict disease-free survival with a discrimination superior to the UICC/AJCC stage groupings. This is explained by a more individualized approach by consideration of more variables of prognostic relevance, among them also some that did not reach the level of significance in a multivariate model. [CITATION_1] The reason is the way the nomogram was created: clinicians were asked for factors that they felt theoretically should be predictive, which were then used as nomogram variables. An alternative way of choosing those variables would have been to perform a univariate and multivariate analysis of variables in the patient database and select those with a significant impact on disease-specific survival as predictors along with factors, which appeared ",
